{"topicSections":[{"title":"Triggers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger","doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/PlainTaskTrigger"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/SwiftUI"],"title":"Extended Modules"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/tasktrigger"]}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Attach async tasks to SwiftUI views using a trigger mechanism."}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"metadata":{"title":"TaskTrigger","symbolKind":"module","role":"collection","modules":[{"name":"TaskTrigger"}],"roleHeading":"Framework","externalID":"TaskTrigger"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"When using Swift’s structured concurrency in SwiftUI it is good practice to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"tie the tasks to the relevant view’s lifetime in order to support task"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"cancellation should the view be dismissed."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"name":"Info","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Usually a task might not take all that long that we would even care for","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"cancellation. But imagine downloading some large amounts of data from a remote","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"server which – depending on the network connection – could take a consiterable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"amount of time. When the user decides to dismiss the view it might be good to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"also cancel the task to not keep doing no longer necessary work.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Of course this does not guarantee that the child tasks will instantly stop but rather","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"they will be informed via "},{"code":"Task.isCancelled","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" that they’ve been cancelled. If or how"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"they handle cancellation is entirely up to the implementation of the child task."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","style":"note"},{"anchor":"The-Problem","text":"The Problem","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This can already be achieved by using the "},{"code":"task(id:priority:_:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" view modifier."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"However this requires additional housekeeping for the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"id"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In a primitive example where we just want to trigger some task we might use a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Bool"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"id"},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@State var triggerTask: Bool = false","","var body: some View {","    Button(\"Do Something\") {","        triggerTask = true","    }","    .task(id: triggerTask) {","        guard triggerTask else { return }","        await someAsyncOperation()","        triggerTask = false","    }","}"]},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We need to check that "},{"code":"triggerTask","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is indeed ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":", and otherwise return.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"We also need to reset "},{"code":"triggerTask","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" at the end of execution. Otherwise another","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"tap wouldn’t trigger the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"task(id:priority:_:)"},{"text":" again.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The first step is crucial becuase we would trigger the task again from in itself"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"when we reset ","type":"text"},{"code":"triggerTask","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" at the end.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This makes even more sense in a more complicated example where we have a list of views"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"where we would like to do something based on some identifier:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@State var triggerTaskId: Int?","","var body: some View {","    List(0..<10) { index in","        Button(\"Item \\(index)\") {","            triggerTaskId = index","        }","    }","    .task(id: triggerTaskId) {","        guard let triggerTaskId else { return }","        await someAsyncOperation(for: triggerTaskId)","        triggerTaskId = nil","    }","}"]},{"name":"Note","style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In this case we have an optional integer and we set it to the index of the button"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in the list once pressed. We need to unwrap the optional value and reset it to "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" afterwards.","type":"text"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This approach, while it really works well, comes with a lot of overhead directly in our view."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Also we have to call the state value directly from within our task which might be cumbersome when we","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"hold the state in a view model.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"The Solution","anchor":"The-Solution","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To make things simpler on the caller’s side let’s wrap all of this functionality inside","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"a simple type ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["@State var trigger = TaskTrigger<Int>()","","var body: some View {","    List(0..<10) { index in","        Button(\"Item \\(index)\") {","            trigger.trigger(value: index)","        }","    }","    .task($trigger) { index in","        await someAsyncOperation(for: index)","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We declare a new state variable "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"trigger"},{"type":"text","text":" and initialize the "},{"code":"TaskTrigger","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" of type ","type":"text"},{"code":"Int","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In our button we call the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger\/trigger(value:id:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" method on our "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"trigger"},{"text":" and pass in our value.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"We attach a new variant of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"task"},{"text":" view modifier to our view and bind it to our ","type":"text"},{"code":"trigger","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The body will only execute when the ","type":"text"},{"code":"trigger","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" was triggered. The value we passed into the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger\/trigger(value:id:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method earlier gets passed into the closure as an argument."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All cancellation related handling, sanity checking, as well as resetting the state is handled"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"automatically behind the scenes.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You might wonder why there’s an optional parameter "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"id"},{"type":"text","text":" on the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger\/trigger(value:id:)"},{"type":"text","text":" method."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"By default this will create a new "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UUID"},{"type":"text","text":" whenever the method is called. This means we can tap the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"same button multiple times and prior operations will get cancelled if they are still running."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In case you don’t want that to happen explicitly set the "},{"code":"id","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter and it won’t cancel"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"prior operations since both the "},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"id"},{"text":" are still the same.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note","name":"Info"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For triggers that don’t need to attach a value, we can simply use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/PlainTaskTrigger","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" (which is a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"typealias for ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"TaskTrigger<Bool>"},{"type":"text","text":"):"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["@State var trigger = PlainTaskTrigger()","","var body: some View {","    Button(\"Do Something\") {","        trigger.trigger()","    }","    .task($trigger) {","        await someAsyncOperation()","    }","}"]}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"references":{"doc://TaskTrigger/documentation/TaskTrigger/TaskTrigger":{"url":"\/documentation\/tasktrigger\/tasktrigger","identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger","type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TaskTrigger"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Trigger async tasks attached to SwiftUI views with support for cancellation.","type":"text"}],"title":"TaskTrigger","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"TaskTrigger"}]},"doc://TaskTrigger/documentation/TaskTrigger/SwiftUI":{"abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/SwiftUI","title":"SwiftUI","url":"\/documentation\/tasktrigger\/swiftui","role":"collection","kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://TaskTrigger/documentation/TaskTrigger":{"role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Attach async tasks to SwiftUI views using a trigger mechanism."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger","title":"TaskTrigger","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/tasktrigger"},"doc://TaskTrigger/documentation/TaskTrigger/TaskTrigger/trigger(value:id:)":{"url":"\/documentation\/tasktrigger\/tasktrigger\/trigger(value:id:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger\/trigger(value:id:)","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"trigger(value:id:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"trigger"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"value"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Value","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:11TaskTriggerAAV5Valuexmfp"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"id"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:10Foundation4UUIDV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UUID"},{"text":"?)","kind":"text"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Triggers the tasks associated with this "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/TaskTrigger","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and passes along a value of type "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Value"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://TaskTrigger/documentation/TaskTrigger/PlainTaskTrigger":{"kind":"symbol","title":"PlainTaskTrigger","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Trigger async tasks attached to SwiftUI views with support for cancellation.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/tasktrigger\/plaintasktrigger","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"PlainTaskTrigger"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/TaskTrigger\/documentation\/TaskTrigger\/PlainTaskTrigger","fragments":[{"text":"typealias","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"PlainTaskTrigger","kind":"identifier"}]}}}